opyright and published with notice) that may be copyrighted.  Responsibility for making an independent legal assessment of an item and securing any necessary permissions ultimately rests with persons desiring to use the item.</p>\n<p>The NEH awardee responsible for producing each digital object is presented in the Chronicling America page display, below the page image  \u2013 e.g. Image produced by the Library of Congress. For more information on current NDNP awardees, see <a href=\"https://www.loc.gov/ndnp/listawardees.html\">https://www.loc.gov/ndnp/listawardees.html</a>.</p>\n<p>For more information on Library of Congress policies and disclaimers regarding rights and reproductions, see <a href=\"https://www.loc.gov/homepage/legal.html\">https://www.loc.gov/homepage/legal.html</a></p>"], "score": 14.504336, "shard": "02", "shelf_id": "sn83045499, 1949-05-03, Edition 1", "site": ["chroniclingamerica"], "source_group": "ndnp/ak", "source_modified": "2000-01-01T12:00:00Z", "subject": ["newspapers", "juneau (alaska)", "juneau", "united states", "alaska"], "subject_headings": ["Juneau (Alaska)--Newspapers", "Alaska--Juneau", "United States--Alaska--Juneau--Juneau"], "subjects": [{"alaska": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:alaska&fo=json"}, {"juneau": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:juneau&fo=json"}, {"juneau (alaska)": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:juneau+%28alaska%29&fo=json"}, {"newspapers": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:newspapers&fo=json"}, {"united states": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:united+states&fo=json"}], "timestamp": "2024-05-22T23:42:18.423Z", "title": "The daily Alaska empire (Juneau, Alaska), May 3, 1949", "type": ["issue"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn83045499/1949-05-03/ed-1/"}, "locations": null, "method": "mets_filesec", "more_like_this": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/sn83045499/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/sn83045499", "https://search.catalog.loc.gov/instances/73faa284-bb24-54ad-a698-625f7a33c98d"], "batch": ["ak_bowheadwhale_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1926", "description": ["Daily (except Saturday) Vol. 29, no. 4346 (Dec. 8, 1926)-v. 99, no. 219 (July 21, 1964). Supplements accompany some numbers. Archived issues are available in digital format from the Library of Congress Chronicling America online collection. J bird was issued with the Daily Alaska empire from <1932-May 16, 1936>, with separate enumeration. It then resumed publishing on its own September 25, 1936. Juneau Alaska empire (DLC)sn 83045498 (OCoLC)9518440"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-06-05T18:25:11.046Z", "group": ["newspaper-titles", "ndnp/newspapers", "catalog-split-11", "catalog", "united-states-newspaper-directory", "main-catalog-split-11"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn83045499/", "image_url": [], "index": 1, "language": ["english"], "latlong": [58.3010372, -134.4246377], "location": ["juneau", "united states", "alaska"], "location_str": "", "lonlat": [-134.4246377, 58.3010372], "number": ["new york pub libr res libr", "2025-07-01t13:40:49.400000", "microfilm master", "online resource", "center for res libr, newsp proj", "abraham lincoln presidential libr", "1", "microfilm service copy", "sn84020657", "2771-2648", "library of congress", "7746", "sn83045499", "sn83045498", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn83045499/1951-12-29/ed-1/", "california state libr", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn83045499/1926-12-08/ed-1/", "wisconsin hist soc, newsp proj", "original", "2024-05-12t17:51:13.897021", "9518436", "huntington libr art gallery & gardens", "franklin d roosevelt libr", "saint bonaventure univ", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["the daily alaska empire (juneau, alaska) 1926-1964", "catalog", "chronicling america", "serial and government publications division", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 40.84567, "shelf_id": "News